triples.name: Genetic programming
triples.relevance: Genetic programming is the foundational evolutionary algorithm concept upon which all compared methods are based.

triples.name: Linear genetic programming
triples.relevance: One of the four genetic programming techniques being compared in this paper, representing programs as linear sequences of instructions.

triples.name: Gene expression programming
triples.relevance: One of the four genetic programming techniques being compared, which combines linear chromosomes with tree-structured phenotypes.

triples.name: Grammatical evolution
triples.relevance: One of the four genetic programming techniques being compared, which uses grammar-based mapping to generate programs.

triples.name: Multi expression programming
triples.relevance: The paper proposes comparing Multi-Expression Programming and demonstrates it has the best overall behavior among the tested methods.

triples.name: List of datasets for machine-learning research
triples.relevance: PROBEN1 is a benchmark dataset with real-world data used in the paper's numerical experiments to test the genetic programming methods.
